You can use [Apache Maven Remote Resources Plugin][1]

&gt; This plugin is used to retrieve JARs of resources from remote
&gt; repositories, process those resources, and incorporate them into JARs
&gt; you build with Maven.
&gt; 
&gt; A very common use-case is the need to package certain resources in a
&gt; consistent way across your organization. For example at Apache, it is
&gt; required that every JAR produced contains a copy of the Apache license
&gt; and a notice file that references all used software in a given project

1. Define in Project A which resources you want to share or better create separate project for shared resources
```xml
    &lt;build&gt;
        &lt;plugins&gt;
            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-remote-resources-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;version&gt;1.7.0&lt;/version&gt;
                &lt;executions&gt;
                    &lt;execution&gt;
                        &lt;goals&gt;
                            &lt;goal&gt;bundle&lt;/goal&gt;
                        &lt;/goals&gt;
                    &lt;/execution&gt;
                &lt;/executions&gt;
                &lt;configuration&gt;
                    &lt;resourcesDirectory&gt;src/test/resources/&lt;/resourcesDirectory&gt;
                    &lt;includes&gt;
                        &lt;include&gt;log4j2.xml&lt;/include&gt;
                        &lt;include&gt;logback-test.xml&lt;/include&gt;
                      &lt;/includes&gt;
                &lt;/configuration&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
        &lt;/plugins&gt;
    &lt;/build&gt;
```
Maven will create [resources bundle file][2] for sharing resources
`${basedir}/target/classes/META-INF/maven/remote-resources.xml`
```xml
&lt;remoteResourcesBundle xsi:schemaLocation=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/remote-resources/1.1.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/remote-resources-1.1.0.xsd&quot;
    xmlns=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/remote-resources/1.1.0&quot;
    xmlns:xsi=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance&quot;&gt;
  &lt;remoteResources&gt;
    &lt;remoteResource&gt;log4j2.xml&lt;/remoteResource&gt;
    &lt;remoteResource&gt;logback-test.xml&lt;/remoteResource&gt;
  &lt;/remoteResources&gt;
  &lt;sourceEncoding&gt;UTF-8&lt;/sourceEncoding&gt;
&lt;/remoteResourcesBundle&gt;
```
See [documentation][3]

2. Configure other modules to use the shared resources
```xml
    &lt;build&gt;
        &lt;plugins&gt;
            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-remote-resources-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;version&gt;1.7.0&lt;/version&gt;
                &lt;configuration&gt;
                    &lt;outputDirectory&gt;[your output directory]&lt;/outputDirectory&gt;
                    &lt;resourceBundles&gt;
                        &lt;!--The resource bundles that will be retrieved and processed. For example: org.test:shared-resources:${project.version}--&gt;
                        &lt;resourceBundle&gt;groupId:artifactId:version[:type[:classifier]]&lt;/resourceBundle&gt; 
                    &lt;/resourceBundles&gt;
                &lt;/configuration&gt;
                &lt;executions&gt;
                    &lt;execution&gt;
                        &lt;goals&gt;
                            &lt;goal&gt;process&lt;/goal&gt;
                        &lt;/goals&gt;
                    &lt;/execution&gt;
                &lt;/executions&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
        &lt;/plugins&gt;
    &lt;/build&gt;
```

See [documentation][4]


*Alternative solution:*
&lt;br&gt;[Apache Maven Dependency Plugin][5]  It can copy and/or unpack artifacts from local or remote repositories to a specified location.
&lt;br&gt;It was described there https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10532274/maven-extract-dependency-resources-before-test
and there https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5292283/use-a-dependencys-resources

**UPDATE:**
&lt;br&gt;Example how to add resources:
```xml
&lt;project&gt;
 ...
 &lt;build&gt;
   ...
   &lt;resources&gt;
     &lt;resource&gt;
       &lt;directory&gt;[your folder 1 here]&lt;/directory&gt;
     &lt;/resource&gt;
     &lt;resource&gt;
       &lt;directory&gt;[your folder 2 here]&lt;/directory&gt;
     &lt;/resource&gt;
   &lt;/resources&gt;
   ...
 &lt;/build&gt;
 ...
&lt;/project&gt;
```
See [documentation][6]


  [1]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-remote-resources-plugin/
  [2]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-remote-resources-plugin/remote-resources.html
  [3]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-remote-resources-plugin/bundle-mojo.html
  [4]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-remote-resources-plugin/process-mojo.html
  [5]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-dependency-plugin/index.html
  [6]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-resources-plugin/examples/resource-directory.html

